It just looks like pixel art of a top-down view of a ceramic baking tray broken on the kitchen floor. The symmetry is lost in the mess of squares and lines all over the place. But yeah, I only noticed that post-solve, and only because I really tried to find something positive about the puzzle :D. I looked and looked, and that was what I got :P.

I get the front page thing though. Poland's most authoritative liberal newspaper, Gazeta Wyborcza (Election Newspaper, so called because it was founded by key opposition figure Adam Michnik in 1989 in the run-up to Poland's first semi-free elections in decades) changed its whole layout in the late 1990s, supposedly to modernise its image. The new one made the whole thing look messy, I thought. I never got used to it.

